      "body" : "It's not ideal, but it is extremely common in software development.\r\nIf you change a `.cpp` or `.h` file the dependencies should be picked up automatically.\r\n*however* if the build system itself is changed (`Makefile.am`, `configure.ac`, ...), it is frequently infeasible to detect the dependencies that need to be recompiled. And for example if some compiler flag was added, everything has to be recompiled either way.\r\n",
